1-) installation mariadb (database)
    - Folder type: There must be a docker file into the srcs/requirements/mariadb/
    - dockerfile: install a mariadb using an alphine-based images
2-) wordpress + PHP-FPM installation
    - Folder type: There must be a docker file into the srcs/requirements/wordpress
        and also a script file that will be automatically set up
    - Connection: must be connected to the mariadb container
    - Functionality: must be able to install wordpress and configure it
3-) Update Docker compose file:
    - services: must be updated to include mariadb and wordpress services
    - volumes: must be updated to include mariadb and wordpress volumes
    - networks: be sure that all containers are connected to the same network "inception"
4-) Missing documentation:
    - README.md: must be updated to include the new configuration
    - USER-DOC.md: It is a guide for users.
    - DEV-DOC.md: It is a guide for developers.~

Check	Command/Action
☐ No credentials in repo	grep -r password .
☐ Makefile at root	ls Makefile
☐ srcs/ folder exists	ls srcs/
☐ README.md exists	ls README.md
☐ USER_DOC.md exists	ls USER_DOC.md
☐ DEV_DOC.md exists	ls DEV_DOC.md
☐ No network: host	grep "network: host" srcs/docker-compose.yml
☐ Has networks section	grep "networks:" srcs/docker-compose.yml
☐ Port 80 blocked	curl http://hpehliva.42.fr (should fail)
☐ Port 443 works	curl -k https://hpehliva.42.fr
☐ TLS 1.2/1.3	openssl s_client -connect hpehliva.42.fr:443
☐ WordPress visible	Browser check
☐ Admin not "admin"	Check username
☐ Volumes in /home/hpehliva/data/	docker volume inspect
☐ DB not empty	Login to MariaDB
☐ Persistence after reboot	Reboot and test

# Reboot your VM
sudo reboot

# After reboot, start again
make

# Verify:
# 1. All containers running
docker compose -f srcs/docker-compose.yml ps

# 2. WordPress still has your previous changes
# 3. Database still has data